						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the central shrine in Svarṇapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikramachōḷa year 7: 1124-25 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete record may palaeographically be assigned to c. 12th century.</p>						

						<p>The epigraph commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti Pūmādu puṇara,</hi> etc., of the king and records the gift of money for maintaining a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to the deity Aḻagiyadēva of Tirupputtūr. Mention is made of <hi rend="italic">śaṅkarappāḍi.</hi> The details of the grant portion and the name of the donor are not found.</p>						

						</summary>
